obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4186  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 6: Liprin-alpha 1 overexpression was shown to disrupt dendritic clustering and surface expression of AMPA receptors. Cultured hippocampal neurons were transfected at DIV14 with either liprin-alpha-1A or liprin-alpha 1, and doubled labeled at DIV20 for overexpressed liprin-alpha 1 and endogenous GluR2/3, endogenous PSD-95, endogenous surface GluR1, or endogenous surface GluR2. Transfected neurons were detected using anti- liprin- alpha 1 antibodies at a low dilution that allowed visualization of cells overexpressing liprin-alpha 1, but not of endogenous liprin- alpha1in untransfected cells.\n\nFig. 7: Liprin-alpha1A was shown to inhibit surface expression of GluR2 but Not GluR1. The same methodology of Fig. 6 was used with cells triple labeled for overexpressed liprin-alpha1 or liprin-alpha1A, surface HA-GluR1 or surface HA-GluR2, and intracellular HA-GluR1 or HA-GluR2.\nThe mammalian expression constructs for liprin-alpha 1 and liprin-alpha 1A and the mouse monoclonal liprin-alpha 1 antibody (1.77) were used from Serra-Pages et al., 1995.. Experimental description: Rat hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from hippocampi dissected from E18 rat embryos as described (Goslin and Banker, 1991)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4186" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

